<div id="node-3473" class="node node-type-story node-promoted node-teaser build-mode-teaser"><div class="node-inner">

  
      <h2 class="title">
      <a href="/node/3473" title="Video: SpringOne 2GX - Tuning Java for Virtual Environments with EM4J">Video: SpringOne 2GX - Tuning Java for Virtual Environments with EM4J</a>
    </h2>
  
  
      <div class="meta">
              <div class="submitted">
          Submitted by Adam Fitzgerald on Wed, 2012-02-15 20:42        </div>
      
              <div class="terms terms-inline"> in <ul class="links inline"><li class="taxonomy_term_4 first last"><a href="/taxonomy/term/4" rel="tag" title="News and announcements
">News and Announcements</a></li>
</ul></div>
          </div>
  
  <div class="content">
    <p> 
<div style="float: right; width:316px; padding: 10px">
<a href="http://www.infoq.com/presentations/Tuning-Java-for-Virtual-with-EM4J"><img height="236" alt="SpringOne 2GX Video: Tuning Java for Virtual Environments with EM4J" width="316" border="0" src="http://www.springsource.org/files/SpringOne2GX2012TuningJavaForVirtualEnvironment.png" /></a>
</div>

As datacenters virtualize more and more workloads, it becomes important to understand the potential impact on the Java servers that may be running your applications. At SpringOne 2GX 2011, <a href="http://blog.springsource.org/author/bcorrie/">Ben Corrie</a> provided a thorough <a href="http://www.infoq.com/presentations/Tuning-Java-for-Virtual-with-EM4J">overview of Java memory management</a>, how things work differently in virtual environments and what you can do about it to avoid problems. This includes a practical introduction to Elastic Memory for Java (EM4J) that is a feature of the <a href="http://www.vmware.com/products/application-platform/vfabric/overview.html">VMware vFabric platform</a>. 
</p>


<p>Many thanks to <a href="http://www.infoq.com">InfoQ</a> for coming to Chicago to record so many of the fantastic <a href="http://www.infoq.com/springone_2gx_2011/">SpringOne 2GX presentations</a>.
</p>

  </div>

  <ul class="links inline"><li class="comment_forbidden first last"></li>
</ul>
</div></div> <!-- /node-inner, /node -->
<div id="node-3472" class="node node-type-story node-promoted node-teaser build-mode-teaser"><div class="node-inner">

  
      <h2 class="title">
      <a href="/node/3472" title="Spring Data MongoDB 1.0.1 GA released">Spring Data MongoDB 1.0.1 GA released</a>
    </h2>
  
  
      <div class="meta">
              <div class="submitted">
          Submitted by ogierke on Wed, 2012-02-15 12:28        </div>
      
              <div class="terms terms-inline"> in <ul class="links inline"><li class="taxonomy_term_4 first last"><a href="/taxonomy/term/4" rel="tag" title="News and announcements
">News and Announcements</a></li>
</ul></div>
          </div>
  
  <div class="content">
    <p>On the way to Spring IO conference I'd like to announce the availability of Spring Data MongoDB 1.0.1. It's mainly a bug fix release covering a few glitches found in the first major release. We've fixed some issues in entity mapping, query execution and added a converter for UUIDs out of the box.</p>
<p><a href="http://www.springsource.com/download/community?project=Spring%20Data%20MongoDB&amp;version=1.0.1.RELEASE">Downloads</a> | <a href="http://static.springsource.org/spring-data/data-mongodb/docs/1.0.1.RELEASE/api/">JavaDocs</a> | <a href="http://static.springsource.org/spring-data/data-mongodb/docs/1.0.1.RELEASE/reference/html/">Reference Documentation</a> | <a href="http://static.springframework.org/spring-data/data-mongodb/docs/1.0.1.RELEASE/changelog.txt">Changelog</a></p>
<p>The release is available from our Maven repository and from Maven Central as well. To learn more about the project, visit the Spring Data <a href="http://www.springsource.org/spring-data/mongodb">MongoDB Page</a>. Looking forward to your feedback on the <a href="http://forum.springsource.org/forumdisplay.php?f=80">forum</a> or in the <a href="https://jira.springsource.org/browse/DATAMONGO">issue tracker</a>.</p>
  </div>

  <ul class="links inline"><li class="comment_forbidden first last"></li>
</ul>
</div></div> <!-- /node-inner, /node -->
